        "subject": "LU-2614 build: Modified lbuild script to build SR-IOV enabled OFED",
        "message": "LU-2614 build: Modified lbuild script to build SR-IOV enabled OFED\n\nTo enable the compilation of the SR-IOV enabled OFED stack provided\nby Mellanox, a different compilation command for the OFED kernel has\nto be used. The SR-IOV features allows the usage of virtualized functions\nwithin a infiniband HCA, and assign them to different VMs simultanously.\nAt the moment neither the 'vanilla' OFED (www.openfabrics.org)\nnort the customised OFED from Mellanox support this feature.\nA new option '--ofed-vm' has been introduced to switch the compilation\non the compilation of the SR-IOV driver.\nThe name of the file to be used is currently hard coded. A separte\noption will be implented to specify the download location in the next\nrelease.\n\nCode changes in download_ofed, build_kernel_ib\n\nSigned-off-by: frank <Frank.Heckes@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Iae8eafda2e7c475e519db6d927bf0c70f23ff70e\n"
      },
